uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.data.controller.impl.ControllerImpl

Class CachedDataAccessController

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.data.controller.impl.ControllerImpl.AbstractDataAccessController
      • uk.ac.ebi.pride.utilities.data.controller.impl.ControllerImpl.CachedDataAccessController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MetaDataAccess, MzGraphDataAccess, PeptideDataAccess, ProteinDataAccess, ProteinGroupDataAccess, QuantDataAccess, DataAccessController
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MzDataControllerImpl, MzMLControllerImpl, MzXmlControllerImpl, PeakControllerImpl, PrideXmlControllerImpl, ReferencedIdentificationController

    public abstract class CachedDataAccessController
extends AbstractDataAccessController
    CachedDataAccessController is abstract class, which enables caching for DataAccessController. Cache is used to store the information used to populate GUI's tables.

    It provides the option to choose different running mode, at the present, there are two modes:

    1.CACHE_ONLY: only get the information from cache. 2.CACHE_AND_SOURCE: it first checks the cache, if not exist, then read from data source.

    Author:
    Rui Wang, Yasset Perez-Riverol

      • isSpectrumBasedOnTitle

        public boolean isSpectrumBasedOnTitle()
        In some cases (WIFF files) the spectrum is referenced using the TITLE instead of using the index. In those cases we need to re-write the SpectraData Object to reflect it. This is a hack of the mzIdentML specification.
        Returns:
        return true if the Spectrum identification title is based on title, special use case for WIFF files.
